During a press briefing aboard Air Force One, White House Deputy Press Secretary Hogan Gidley discussed several topics. He mentioned that President Trump will be leading a roundtable discussion in White Sulphur Springs, West Virginia, featuring West Virginia-based companies, families, and elected officials who support the President's economic agenda. Gidley also confirmed an upcoming visit to the White House by German Chancellor Angela Merkel. Regarding Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Scott Pruitt, Gidley stated that if the President has confidence in someone, they stay, but the reports of Pruitt's conduct are being looked into. Gidley also mentioned that preparations are being made for talks with China about trade, but he couldn't provide specifics. He emphasized that no tariffs have been put in place yet and that the President aims to protect American workers, businesses, and farmers. Additionally, Gidley mentioned that the number of National Guard troops deployed to the border will be as many as needed, and the federal government expects all governors to support their efforts to protect citizens.